"{\"uid\": \"cnn.com-2024-07-25-opinions-olympics-swimming-pools-drowning-children-cullen-jones\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Follow:  Editor's Note:Cullen Jones is a two-time Olympian and a four-time Olympic medalist.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 92, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 23, \"end\": 35, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cullen_Jones\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cullen Jones\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cullen_Jones\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cullen_Jones\"}, {\"begin\": 50, \"end\": 58, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999999504325, \"rank\": 4.951657724620504e-11, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He partners with the USA Swimming Foundation and Make a Splash Foundation to provide drowning prevention education and motivational speaking.\", \"from\": 93, \"to\": 234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 114, \"end\": 126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USA Swimming\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow him on X and Instagram at @CullenJones.\", \"from\": 235, \"to\": 281, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The opinions expressed in this essay are his own.\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 331, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Readmore opinionat CNN.\", \"from\": 332, \"to\": 355, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 351, \"end\": 354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3756500553826487e-14, \"text\": \"CNN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After nearly drowning at the age of five, I could never have dreamt that one day I would swim competitively, let alone twice at the Olympics - or that I would become thefirst Black swimmer to hold a world record.\", \"from\": 357, \"to\": 569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The incident happened, as these occurrences often do, in a setting where kids are supposed to have fun, on a water ride at an amusement park just outside of Philadelphia.\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 728, \"end\": 740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philadelphia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8055223032490724e-16, \"text\": \"Philadelphia\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philadelphia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philadelphia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"My parents were nearby and a lifeguard was on duty, but somehow the responsible adults lost sight of me long enough for me to end up underwater.\", \"from\": 743, \"to\": 887, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I had to be resuscitated by a lifeguard and felt traumatized by the ordeal, but luckily did not suffer any long-term physical effects from it.\", \"from\": 888, \"to\": 1030, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And my parents wasted no time in signing me up for swimming lessons.\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1099, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Grit and perseverance guided me to where I am today.\", \"from\": 1101, \"to\": 1153, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ultimately, my journey - like that of many swimmers competing at this summer's Olympics in Paris - was only made possible by my ability to access a public pool.\", \"from\": 1154, \"to\": 1314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1245, \"end\": 1250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999915712579, \"rank\": 8.428518297568093e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But that access did not come easy: I took two buses and traveled 30 minutes from my elementary school to the Rutgers Aquatic Center in Newark, New Jersey.\", \"from\": 1315, \"to\": 1469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1424, \"end\": 1431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rutgers_University\", \"score\": 0.9999999999276952, \"rank\": 5.90485483843716e-11, \"text\": \"Rutgers\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rutgers_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rutgers_University\"}, {\"begin\": 1458, \"end\": 1468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.44435160373197e-18, \"text\": \"New Jersey\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It became my sanctuary from the gang violence and poverty-stricken area I grew up in.\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1555, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whether to prevent a near-drowning like mine or to cool off during increasingly hot summer months, accessible public pools are vital to the health of entire communities.\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1726, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, too many communities today lack an affordable community pool of their own.\", \"from\": 1727, \"to\": 1816, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Accessible public pools are vital to the health of entire communities.\\\"\", \"from\": 1818, \"to\": 1890, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Majority-Black communities continue to experience thelegacy of structural racismfrom when pools were among the most segregated public places in our country.\", \"from\": 1894, \"to\": 2050, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many of the stigmas have emerged from that history and have become so deeply embedded in our culture that we even repeat them to each other: \\\"You know Black people do not swim!\\\"\", \"from\": 2051, \"to\": 2228, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"is a phrase that many people in the community have internalized and tell each other - and ourselves - masking the systemic injustices around water access and safety that explain why so few of us become proficient swimmers.\", \"from\": 2229, \"to\": 2451, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Have you ever wondered why backyard pools became so popular?\", \"from\": 2453, \"to\": 2513, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As Heather McGhee writes inher book, \\\"The Sum of Us: What Racism Costs Everyone and How We Can Prosper Together\\\":\\\"Millions of White Americans who once swam in public for free began to pay rather than swim for free with Black people.\\\"\", \"from\": 2515, \"to\": 2748, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2518, \"end\": 2532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heather_McGhee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Heather McGhee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heather_McGhee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Heather_McGhee\"}, {\"begin\": 2641, \"end\": 2656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_Americans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.685511217689424e-36, \"text\": \"White Americans\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_Americans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, there are more than10 million private swimming poolsin the United States, according toan industry trade group, compared with just over 300,000 public ones.\", \"from\": 2750, \"to\": 2912, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2816, \"end\": 2829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999418078788792, \"rank\": 0.0005822600406247206, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Public pools\\\" includes those associated with schools, hotels and other exclusive community spaces, so the number of pools that are truly accessible to the public is even smaller.\", \"from\": 2913, \"to\": 3092, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Related articleOpinion: The simple reason why so many adults can not swim  In the 1960s, many public pools were filled with concrete or destroyed to avoid allowing Black Americans to swim in them.\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3290, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3258, \"end\": 3263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Americans\", \"score\": 0.9985221235332318, \"rank\": 0.0014800638181301656, \"text\": \"Black\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African_Americans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, park managersopted to shut down the Historic Audubon Park Natatoriumin New Orleans, the largest public pool in the South, rather than see it integrated.\", \"from\": 3291, \"to\": 3452, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is just one of many examples of how racism and discrimination led to the destruction and disinvestment of public pools, the consequences of which are still evident today.\", \"from\": 3453, \"to\": 3628, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC)reported in Maythat more than one-third (36.8%) of Black adults reported that they do not know how to swim, compared with 15% of all adults.\", \"from\": 3630, \"to\": 3822, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Black children ages 10-14 years drown in swimming pools at a rate that is almost8 times higherthan White children.\", \"from\": 3823, \"to\": 3937, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Income, too, plays a huge role in determining one's ability to swim: A2017 studyfrom the USA Swimming Foundation found that 79% of children in families with incomes under $50,000 have no or low swimming experience.\", \"from\": 3938, \"to\": 4152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4027, \"end\": 4039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USA Swimming\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Access to safe public pools - both as a public health necessity and source of joy in communities - should be the gold standard everywhere.\\\"\", \"from\": 4154, \"to\": 4294, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These disparities are far from a coincidence; this is by design.\", \"from\": 4298, \"to\": 4362, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to limiting pool access, discrimination and disinvestment in majority-Black neighborhoods has led to food deserts and a lack of green spaces, community services and public gathering places - a gutting of what helps communities thrive.\", \"from\": 4363, \"to\": 4609, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For many people, what used to be considered \\\"third places\\\" - venues where individuals could spend time relaxing outside of the home and workplace - have become exclusive outposts easily accessible and adequately funded only in wealthier, White neighborhoods.\", \"from\": 4611, \"to\": 4869, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4849, \"end\": 4854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_people\", \"score\": 0.999993686494157, \"rank\": 6.313545831865346e-06, \"text\": \"White\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Third places are incredibly important for public health and wellbeing however because they give people a place to socialize and build community.\", \"from\": 4870, \"to\": 5014, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Related articleOpinion: The summer skill every kid in America should have  Our communities deserve better.\", \"from\": 5016, \"to\": 5122, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lawmakers and community leaders should act on the CDC's recent recommendation to build and revitalize public pools to increase access to swimming for all people.\", \"from\": 5123, \"to\": 5284, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5173, \"end\": 5176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Centers_for_Disease_Control_and_Prevention\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.1525423204241664e-23, \"text\": \"CDC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Centers_for_Disease_Control_and_Prevention\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Centers_for_Disease_Control_and_Prevention\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The answer is notanother splash pad.The answer is increasing access both to pools and the safety programs and information that will keep kids safe when using them.\", \"from\": 5285, \"to\": 5448, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We also need better national data about our public pool system that goes beyond project- or funding-specific tracking.\", \"from\": 5450, \"to\": 5568, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, while theTrust for Public Land's mapping tooldoes a good job tracking pools that are federally funded through Community Project Funding grants, it does not capture the number of free or low-cost public pools around the country.\", \"from\": 5569, \"to\": 5809, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Our summers are only getting hotter, and access to safe public pools - both as a public health necessity and source of joy in communities - should be the gold standard everywhere.\", \"from\": 5811, \"to\": 5990, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As you cheer on your favorite swimmers in Paris, think about what you can do in your community to ensure everyone feels the joy of swimming.\", \"from\": 5992, \"to\": 6132, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6034, \"end\": 6039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999915712579, \"rank\": 8.428518297568093e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic medals might be for a privileged few, but everyone has a right to cool off and gain potentially life-saving swimming skills.\", \"from\": 6133, \"to\": 6265, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 2025 Cable News Network.\", \"from\": 6267, \"to\": 6293, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A Warner Bros.\", \"from\": 6294, \"to\": 6308, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6296, \"end\": 6302, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warner_Bros.\", \"score\": 0.5748396086673204, \"rank\": 0.7396147197124181, \"text\": \"Warner\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warner_Bros.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warner_Bros.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Discovery Company.\", \"from\": 6309, \"to\": 6327, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6309, \"end\": 6318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Discovery_Channel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.503632895126835e-15, \"text\": \"Discovery\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Discovery_Channel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Discovery_Channel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All Rights Reserved.CNN Sans \\u2122 & \\u00a9 2016 Cable News Network.\", \"from\": 6328, \"to\": 6387, \"entities\": []}]}"